  "note": "Hasbrouck (1995) information share + Gonzalo-Granger (1995) permanent-component share, on 1s last-price tape mids per matched contract, dropping non-cointegrated pairs (ADF p>=0.10 on the (1,-1) spread). >50% = that venue leads price discovery. The honest unit is the match: headline is the median across matches of each match's median contract share. Hasbrouck gives a lo/hi band per contract (Cholesky ordering); GG is unique. Computed on MID moves, so robust to the ~59% WS trade-direction problem (arXiv 2604.24366).",
